==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Splendor
<hw>Splen"dor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos><ety>[L. fr.
<ets>splendere</ets> to shine: cf. F. <ets>splendeur</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Great brightness; brilliant luster; brilliancy; <as>as,
the <ex>splendor</ex> of the sun</as>.</def> <rj><au>B.
Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Magnificence; pomp; parade; <as>as, the
<ex>splendor</ex> of equipage, ceremonies, processions, and the
like</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Rejoice in <xex>splendor</xex> of mine
own.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Brilliancy; glory; <as>as, the <ex>splendor</ex> of
a victory</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Luster; brilliancy; magnifience; gorgeousness;
display; showiness; pomp; parade; grandeur.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Splendorous</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Splendrous</ent>⟦br⟧
